    "title": {
      "__cdata": "Writerly Resolutions for a New Year with Meg Gaertner - Writescast 027"
    },
    "link": "https://ryanrcampbell.com/podcast/writescast027/",
    "pubDate": "Fri, 29 Dec 2017 06:05:13 +0000",
    "creator": {
      "__cdata": "rrcampbell"
    },
    "guid": "https://ryanrcampbell.com/?post_type=podcast&#038;p=4780",
    "description": "",
    "encoded": [
      {
        "__cdata": "[caption id=\"attachment_4781\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"189\"]<img class=\"wp-image-4781 \" src=\"https://ryanrcampbell.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Gaertner-Author-Photo-e1513281414815-242x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"189\" height=\"234\"> Meg Gaertner[/caption]\n\nMeg Gaertner returns to the writescast to discuss goals: those we set out to achieve in 2017, whether we achieved them, and what we learned along the way. Then we look forward to 2018 (and beyond!), all in the interest of helping YOU maximize your own goal-oriented success.\n\nMeg Gaertner is a graduate student at Antioch University’s MFA in Creative Writing program. She writes YA speculative fiction, adult fantasy, and middle grade contemporary, and she has a book review published in the literary journal&nbsp;<i>Lunch Ticket</i>. When she’s not writing, she’s out swing-dancing or facilitating Qoya movement classes. She blogs at&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.meggaertner.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?hl=en&amp;q=http://www.meggaertner.com&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1513367721963000&amp;usg=AFQjCNGAtLnkpo5I8erbyBBpz0DhKkpVrg\">www.meggaertner.com</a>, and you can connect with her at <a href=\"http://www.twitter.com/megaertner\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">@MEGaertner</a> on Twitter or <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/meg.gaertner/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">meg.gaertner</a> on Instagram.\n\nIn this episode, I mention a handful of stories and articles I wrote that were published this year. You can find them at the below links.\n\n\"Wool\" -&nbsp;<em><a href=\"http://five2onemagazine.com/wool-r-r-campbell-flash-fiction-thesideshow/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Five:2:One Magazine's #thesideshow</a>\n</em>\"What It Is To Smell Of Man\" -&nbsp;<em><a href=\"http://eroticreviewmagazine.com/fiction/what-it-is-to-smell-of-man/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Erotic Review</a>&nbsp;</em>(NSFW, 18+)\n\"40,000 to Flesh: How I Journaled My Way to Character\" -&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.najowrimo.org/40000-flesh-journaled-way-character/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>National Journal Writing Month</em></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href=\"https://ryanrcampbell.com/podcast-download/4780/writescast027.mp3?ref=new_window\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Click here to listen to this episode.</a>"
      },
      {
        "__cdata": "Meg Gaertner returns to the writescast to discuss goals: those we set out to achieve in 2017, whether we achieved them, and what we learned along the way. Then we look forward to 2018 (and beyond!), all in the interest of helping YOU maximize your own goal-oriented success as well."
      }
    ],
